books.name: Stiven Kinga
books.about: Stephen Edwin King ( Eng. Stephen Edwin King ; b. 21 September 1947 , Portland , Maine , USA ) - American writer, author of more than 200 works, including more than 50 best-selling books in the styles of horrors ( Eng. Horror ), fantasy , thriller , mystic . Also wrote under the pseudonym Richard Bachman ( Eng. Richard Bachman) It sold more than 350 million copies of his novels and collections of stories. On the basis of his stories a series of films was filmed, as well as painted comics. Awarded the medal "For a Special Contribution to American Literature." In 2003, the National Book Fund awarded him a medal for outstanding contributions to American literature. He also received awards for his contribution to literature throughout his career, such as the Contribution to the World Fantasy Award (2004), was awarded by the Canadian Book Sellers Association (2007) and the Grandmaster Award from American Writers of Mystics (2007).
